4. Explain the concept of encapsulation in Java classes and provide an example.
Encapsulation is one of the pillars of the OOPs concept in java it is 
the mechanism of bundling the data and the mehod eithin a single unit 
called as class it can be achieved by using different asscess
 modifier  Public Private Proteced for the case of the Proteced modifier 
 the properties and the behavior of the class having protected modifier can be achieved
 within the same class or child class of that parent class only